        "innovation_claims": [
          "---\ntitle: Self-Evolving Multi-Agent Systems via Decentralized Memory\narxiv_id: 2605.22721\nauthors: Guangya Hao, Yunbo Long, Zhuokai Zhao\nurl: https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.22721\n---\n\n## Abstract\n\nSelf-evolving multi-agent systems (MAS) have emerged as a promising route to LLM agents that continually improve from experience, with persistent memory at their foundation",
          "We propose DecentMem, a decentralized memory framework in which each agent maintains its own dual-pool memory -- an exploitation pool of consolidated past trajectories and an exploration pool of LLM-generated candidates for unseen contexts",
          "Theoretically, we prove that this design guarantees global reachability of the solution space and achieves $O(\\log T)$ cumulative regret, matching the stochastic bandit lower bound up to constants",
          "## Full Text\n\n# **Self-Evolving Multi-Agent Systems via Decentralized Memory** \n\n**Guangya Hao[1] Yunbo Long[1] Zhuokai Zhao[2]** 1University of Cambridge 2University of Chicago \n\n## **Abstract** \n\nSelf-evolving multi-agent systems (MAS) have emerged as a promising route to LLM agents that continually improve from experience, with persistent memory at their foundation",
          "We propose **DECENTMEM** , a _decentralized_ memory framework in which each agent maintains its own dual-pool memory \u2014 an exploitation pool of consolidated past trajectories and an exploration pool of LLM-generated candidates for unseen contexts",
          "Theoretically, we prove that this design guarantees global reachability of the solution space and achieves _O_ (log _T_ ) cumulative regret, matching the stochastic bandit lower bound up to constants",
          "Figure 1: Compared to traditional centralized memory frameworks, DECENTMEM provides the first decentralized memory framework with adaptability to various MAS frameworks",
          "that makes collaboration valuable in the first place, rather than drive the system toward a single shared strategy",
          "Motivated by these limitations, we propose **DECENTMEM** , a decentralized self-evolving memory framework for LLM-based MAS",
          "Under this formulation, we prove that DECENTMEM achieves global reachability over each agent\u2019s local solution subspace and attains _O_ (log _T_ ) cumulative regret, order-optimal against the \u2126(log _T_ ) bandit lower bound [14]"
